<section class="quantum-vacuum">
    <h2>Quantum Vacuum & Nothingness</h2>
    
    <div class="vacuum-visualization">
        <div class="quantum-field">
            <div class="virtual-particles">
                <div class="particle-pair p1"></div>
                <div class="particle-pair p2"></div>
                <div class="particle-pair p3"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="field-fluctuations"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="physics-concepts">
        <div class="concept-card">
            <h3>Vacuum Energy</h3>
            <div class="formula">
                ΔE·Δt ≥ ℏ/2
            </div>
            <div class="animation-container">
                <div class="energy-fluctuation"></div>
            </div>
            <p>
                The quantum vacuum is not empty but filled with fluctuating fields and 
                virtual particles, demonstrating that "nothingness" has physical properties.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-card">
            <h3>Casimir Effect</h3>
            <div class="formula">
                F = -π²ℏcA/240d⁴
            </div>
            <div class="animation-container">
                <div class="casimir-plates">
                    <div class="plate"></div>
                    <div class="virtual-field"></div>
                    <div class="plate"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p>
                Quantum vacuum fluctuations create measurable forces between objects, 
                proving the physical reality of "empty" space.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="concept-card">
            <h3>Cosmic Inflation</h3>
            <div class="formula">
                H² = (8πG/3)ρ
            </div>
            <div class="animation-container">
                <div class="universe-expansion"></div>
            </div>
            <p>
                The universe's rapid expansion from quantum fluctuations suggests that 
                existence itself may have emerged from quantum nothingness.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    .quantum-vacuum {
        margin: 4rem 0;
        padding: 2rem;
        background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.2);
        border-radius: 12px;
    }

    h2 {
        text-align: center;
        color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .vacuum-visualization {
        height: 200px;
        margin: 2rem 0;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.3);
        border-radius: 8px;
    }

    .quantum-field {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
    }

    .virtual-particles {
        position: absolute;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
    }

    .particle-pair {
        position: absolute;
        width: 10px;
        height: 10px;
        background: rgb(var(--accent-light));
        border-radius: 50%;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: particleFluctuation 4s infinite;
    }

    .p1 { left: 30%; top: 40%; animation-delay: 0s; }
    .p2 { left: 60%; top: 50%; animation-delay: 1.3s; }
    .p3 { left: 45%; top: 30%; animation-delay: 2.6s; }

    .field-fluctuations {
        position: absolute;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        background: radial-gradient(
            circle at center,
            rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.2) 0%,
            transparent 70%
        );
        animation: fieldFluctuation 6s infinite;
    }

    .physics-concepts {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-top: 3rem;
    }

    .concept-card {
        padding: 1.5rem;
        background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.3);
        border-radius: 8px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.2);
    }

    .concept-card h3 {
        color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .formula {
        text-align: center;
        font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        margin: 1rem 0;
        color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
    }

    .animation-container {
        height: 150px;
        margin: 1rem 0;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .energy-fluctuation {
        position: absolute;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg,
            transparent,
            rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.3),
            transparent
        );
        animation: energyWave 3s infinite;
    }

    .casimir-plates {
        position: relative;
        height: 100%;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: space-around;
        align-items: center;
    }

    .plate {
        width: 80%;
        height: 10px;
        background: rgb(var(--accent-light));
    }

    .virtual-field {
        width: 100%;
        height: 60px;
        background: repeating-linear-gradient(
            90deg,
            transparent,
            rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.2) 20px,
            transparent 40px
        );
        animation: fieldOscillation 2s infinite;
    }

    .universe-expansion {
        position: absolute;
        width: 20px;
        height: 20px;
        background: rgb(var(--accent-light));
        border-radius: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        top: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        animation: expand 4s infinite;
    }

    @keyframes particleFluctuation {
        0%, 100% { opacity: 0; transform: scale(0); }
        50% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }
    }

    @keyframes fieldFluctuation {
        0%, 100% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 0.2; }
        50% { transform: scale(1.5); opacity: 0.4; }
    }

    @keyframes energyWave {
        0% { transform: translateX(-100%) scaleY(0.5); }
        50% { transform: translateX(0%) scaleY(1); }
        100% { transform: translateX(100%) scaleY(0.5); }
    }

    @keyframes fieldOscillation {
        0%, 100% { opacity: 0.3; }
        50% { opacity: 0.7; }
    }

    @keyframes expand {
        0% { transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1); opacity: 1; }
        100% { transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(20); opacity: 0; }
    }
</style>